Coefficient-ordering convention
-------------------------------
This file uses the SIARC F(2,4) leading-first coefficient convention
recorded in repo memory `f1-base-d2d4-complete-2026-04-22`, namely

    a_coeffs = (a2, a1, a0)   with   a(n) = a2 * n^2 + a1 * n + a0
    b_coeffs = (b1, b0)       with   b(n) = b1 * n + b0

This is the convention of `f1_base_computation.py` and the relay 098
spec (Phase B B1). PCF-1 v1.3 (the published transcendence-dichotomy
paper p12) uses the inverse role convention (a degree 1, b degree 2)
under names (alpha, beta, gamma, delta, epsilon). The two conventions
enumerate the same d=2 PCF family up to a label swap a <-> b; see
`discrepancy_log.json` D-D3 for the explicit translation table.

