-- B6.  PCF limit operator  L = b(0) + K
-- ============================================================

/--
The continued-fraction limit `L = b(0) + K(a_n / b_n)` where `b(0)`
is the constant term of the `b` polynomial added OUTSIDE the K-fold,
per the conventional Wallis-seed expansion of PCF-1 v1.3 § 1.1
equation `eq:PCF`:

    L = b_0 + a_1 / (b_1 + a_2 / (b_2 + ...))

In the SIARC F(2,4) convention `b(0) = b0` is the constant offset.
Convergence depends on the Perron-Poincare structure of the d=2
family; the Lean type is `ℝ` (the formal real) since the limit is
in general transcendental.

